to the Menu." "To place a bomb, press\nENTER or SPACE.\nBreakable walls won't\nsurvive the explosion.\n\nAfter laying a bomb,\ndont stay close so you\ndont go out with it." "Levels may contain ENEMIES.\nExplode them to be able to\npass to the next level.\nBeware: if you touch them,\nyou die.\n\nAnd keep in mind that you may\nonly lay one bomb at a time\nfor now. ;)" "In this level there are\ntwo powerups hidden below\nbreakable walls. Take them,\nand you'll have them for the\nrest of the chapter.\n\nOne of them increases to 4 the\nbomb laying limit, whilst \nthe other increases the\nexplosion area.\n\nP.S.: explosions go through \nwalls" "This is a scroll. From now\non, this will be the way\ninformation will be shown\nto you inside the levels.\nThe scroll will be destroyed\nonce read.\n\nAlso: From this moment forth,\nthe exit will be hidden beneath\nbreakable walls. Can you find\nit? (yes)" "Levels may have different\nsizes, but they'll never\ngo off-screen.\n\nThey may also have a time\nlimit. Complete the level\nbefore time runs out or lose\na life.\n\nDon't worry. Time is paused\nwhile in a scroll.\n\nTime can be seen on the\nupper part of the screen." "Some levels will have NPCs\nthat are not ENEMIES. They\ndon't  need to be blown up\nto pass to the next level.\n\nThey also don't cause your\ndeath on contact.\n\nYou can safely ignore them." "The last level of a chapter\nwill have an ELEVATOR (like\nthis 'E' south). Take it \nto go to the next chapter.\n\n(This will end the tutorial!)" "life is misery" "Beloved, I am here to tell you\nthat the temple is ready.\n\nHammurabi is already here\nwith us. Soon we'll discover\nhow to keep him alive for\nall eternity.\n\nI'll keep in touch through\nthese clay tablets" "Beloved, something awful\nhas befallen us today.\nEnemies of Marduk have tried\nto invade our temple. We \nmanaged to defend, thank to\nthese sentinel statues we\nmanaged to assemble. They\nshould patrol the temple\nautonomously now.\n\nDespite this, we are still\nsieged! We cannot leave! how\nwill I send you these tablets?" "Beloved,\n\nWe have no food nor water.\nThe King will not survive for\nmuch longer.\n\nWe will have to leave the\nresults of our research here,\nuseless. What we have found is\nsimply not enough.\n\nForgive me for leaving so soon." "* You have found the Edict\nof Immortality." "ANNO MMCCCLV\nAB URBE CONDITA\n\n\"As long as you live, let the\nworld see you, and don't make\nyourself miserable; life is \nshort, and Time demands his \ndue.\" -- Seikilos" "I admit that I'd rather end\nup like the astrologers than\nanguish for eternity in\noverwhelming guilt like the\nlegionaries.\n\nBut I, myself, blame them\nnot. Anyone who received\nimmortality at the cost\nof the Imperator would also\ngo mad.\n" "I've spent a few years\nkeenly listening to the\nmurmurs of the surviving\narchitects. From what I've\nunderstood, after all these\nyears, they're still trying\nto figure out how to save\nthe Imperator.\n\nPlease, spare them from\ndeath. They are not enemies." "If anyone found the reason\nwhy the formation had gone\nwrong in such an unfortunate\nway, would any of them\nunderstand?\n\nMaybe if it hadn't been\nso much time since then...\nMaybe..." "Rest in Peace,\nImperator Hadrianus.\n\n* You have found the\nEmperor Hadrian\nAstrological\nFormation." "Press ENTER to close." "A fatal exception has occurred." "Press 4 to close the game." "1. EDIT" "2. SETTINGS" "3. CREDITS" "4. EXIT" "Choose an option:" "1. NEW" "2. LOAD" "Enter file name:" "File not found!" "Esc. RETURN" "1. LANGUAGE" "2. MUTE" "2. UNMUTE" "Choose language:" "1. Portugues Brasileiro" "2. English (US)" "3. Boat" "9. RETURN" "Untitled" "Esc -" "Options" "Tiles" "NPCs" "1. Load Texture" "2. Resize Map" "3. Save" "4. Save as..." "Esc. Return to editor" "9. Exit to Main Menu" "Resize with W A S D" "W. Decrease height\nA. Decrease width\nS. Increase height\nD. Increase width" "Enter. Confirm" "Invalid file name!" "Level saved successfully." "An e